h3. Issue Summary

When trying to publish a rule where there is a "Log work" action and set to copy the value from a field (created, updated, etc) on "Date started" it does not allow to publish and appear the following error message:
{code:java}
An unknown error occurred. Please reload and try again.
{code}
 !Screen Shot 2020-09-14 at 18.01.29.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new rule with any trigger;
# Add the "Log Work" action and set to copy a value from a date/time field (as the screenshot below);
# Click to publish.

h3. Expected Results
Publish the rule without any errors

h3. Actual Results
Errors when publishing the rule. Found only an error 500 in a POST.
{code:java}
An unknown error occurred. Please reload and try again.
{code}

h3. Workaround

Use smart value, for example: 
{code:java}
{{issue.created}}
{code}

At this time the only way to clear a field resolution would be by adding a post-function in a workflow that does that as referred on the following article:
 * [Best practices on using the "Resolution" field|https://confluence.atlassian.com/cloudkb/best-practices-on-using-the-resolution-field-968660796.html#Bestpracticesonusingthe%22Resolution%22field-Thefollowinginstructionsaremeanttocorrectpreviousissuesthathavetheresolutionfieldincorrectlyset.]

Nowadays, we can edit the resolution via REST API but we can't clear its value. It would be nice to have the option to clear the value via REST API.
h3. Suggestion
{code:java}
"fields": {
    "resolution": { "name": "" }
}
{code}
Or even by simply setting as null.
{code:java}
"fields": {
     "resolution": null
}
{code}
